cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with estimating distance from monocular images using deep learning methods. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes a solution to the scale ambiguity problem in vSLAM/VO, which is a common problem in robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a deep recurrent convolutional neural network for distance estimation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel end-to-end approach for distance estimation using deep learning methods. 
- cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper presents a new method for distance estimation from monocular images, which is a common problem in the CVPR community.
